                  <li><div id="res824006229" class="bucket listitem simplelistitem">
      <h3>'I Hate You, Man': Questlove On Just Blaze's Maddening Genius</h3>
   <div class="listitem-inner">
            <div id="res824006954" class="bucketwrap image medium">
                  <div class="imagewrap" data-crop-type="">
    <a href="https://www.npr.org/2020/03/31/823993877/questlove-just-blaze-producer-sampling-maddening-genius">
        <img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2020/03/30/justblaze_still_sq-67db113537b868f78676f70cb3a2b34a4bede186-s800-c15.jpg" data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2020/03/30/justblaze_still_sq-67db113537b868f78676f70cb3a2b34a4bede186-s800.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  alt="Just Blaze" />
    </a>
</div>
<div class="credit-caption">
    <div class="caption-wrap">
        <div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption">
        </div>


    </div>

    <span class="credit" aria-label="Image credit">
        <a href="https://www.npr.org/2020/03/30/823993877/questlove-just-blaze-producer-sampling-maddening-genius" target="_blank">
        NPR
        </a>
    </span>
</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bucketblock">
                  <p>The Roots' drummer and <em data-stringify-type="italic">Tonight Show </em>bandleader picks apart exactly why fellow producer Just Blaze's talent for finding and flipping samples in unexpected combinations is both inspiring and infuriating.</p><p><a href="https://www.npr.org/2020/03/30/823993877/questlove-just-blaze-producer-sampling-maddening-genius" target="_blank">Read the essay by <strong>QUESTLOVE</strong></a></p>
      </div>
      
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKETBLOCK" -->
   </div>
   
<!-- END CLASS="LISTITEM-INNER" -->
